    {
        "content": "<p>Hey, quick question: is it possible to have a diamond-shaped extension of structures: something like two structures extending a given one, and a third being an extension of both? <br>\nMy motivation is the following: there is a notion of prefunctors between quivers, and I'd like to be able to talk about isomorphisms of quivers, and separately of morphisms of quivers commuting with certain other morphisms (covers). The two are orthogonal, and I'd like to be able then to define <code>isomorphisms that commute with covers</code> as an extension of both. Lean complains that the common field is defined already, when trying to do that.</p>\n<p>This is what I mean (with custom notation and variables not included): </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">section</span> <span class=\"n\">cover_automorphisms</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">iso</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">quiver</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">quiver</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"kd\">extends</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚ü∂</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inv_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚ü∂</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">left_inv</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">to_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚â´</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">inv_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">ùüô</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">right_inv</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">inv_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚â´</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">to_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">ùüô</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">cover_endo</span> <span class=\"kd\">extends</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">U</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚ü∂</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">U</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cover</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">to_prefunctor</span> <span class=\"bp\">‚â´</span><span class=\"n\">q</span> <span class=\"n\">œÜ</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">structure</span> <span class=\"n\">cover_auto</span> <span class=\"kd\">extends</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">iso</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">),</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">cover_endo</span> <span class=\"n\">œÜ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">end</span> <span class=\"n\">cover_automorphisms</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 310216312,
        "sender_full_name": "R√©mi Bottinelli",
        "timestamp": 1668523497
